One of the largest and one of the oldest masjid of the town
It has separate wadu Khana, a houz, toilets, large number of water outlets even at burial ground (khaber-e-stan) and well furnished mats with decent lighting and good sound system. The recitation of the imam during namaz is astounding. Namaz with qazi is really extraordinary experience.
The khaber-e-stan itself is one of the biggest of the town, well maintained by the in-house staff of the masjid, it has its own freezer facilities, guzul facilities at guzul-kana free for the poor and service to all with minuscule charges.

Definite recommendation especially for Friday namaz.

Ameenpeer Dargah is a sufi shrine located in the Kadapa City in Andhra Pradesh, India.[1]

This Dargah or Asthana (shrine) is also called Asthana-e-Magdoom Ilahi (astnh mkhdwm lhy). It is located in Asthana-e-Magdoom Ilahi Dargah complex, locally known as Badi Dargah, Pedda Dargah (Telugu) in Kadapa (Cuddapah) city. It is known for its preaching of communal harmony.] It is claimed folk that the saints of the shrine are the descendants of the Islamic prophet, Muhammad.

History of Ameen Peer Dargah

The masjid is believed to be constructed in 1683. It was originally a grave place for the two Sufi saints Perullah Hussaini and Arufulla Hussaini II. The then Nawab of Sidhout Taluk, Nawab Nek nam Khan changed the name of this place to Neknamabaad on the advice of Perullah Hussaini. Neknamabaad eventually became Kadapa.

This is a super cool place. Very good environment with all the facilities needed for recurring Salah/Namaz. It has a ground and first floors exclusively for prayers, for iftar etc.

Recently the ground floor is facilitated with Air Conditioners with new false ceiling, it has the generator, wide spaces for wudu and good RO drinking water 24/7 available for everybody at the main gate. I have seen in Summers people from all walks of life and from different religions come and take away the cool RO purified drinking water 24/7. In fact few available and birds also come and drink water from this place.

In the last ten days of the month of Ramadan, every year, the "tak raths" are observed. Prominent people from different places from the entire country spend their nights. Also, after night prayers, Share food and desserts are organized.

Also this is one of the major landmark in 7 roads circle because 7 roads circle is a very big area and people find it difficult and gets confused and this masjid helps a great way to new commuters.

Overall this is one of the best places. I highly rate and recommend this place.
